[cron:8b380d56-7314-4ba9-b4c4-ea11d3e5ca6f PR Review Patrol (High Frequency)] PR patrol for bills-bot.

Repo: /home/bill/.openclaw/workspace-build/bills-bot/

⚠️ CRITICAL RULE: Only check PRs authored by Bill (BillChirico) or by Pip Build / sub-agents. Do NOT check, fix, or address PRs from anyone else (other contributors, bots like coderabbitai, dependabot[bot], renovate[bot]) unless Bill has explicitly told you to.

Do this each run:
1) List open PRs in BillChirico/bills-bot.
2) Filter to ONLY Bill's PRs and Pip Build's PRs. Skip everything else.
3) For eligible PRs, check BOTH:
   a) Unresolved inline review threads (paginate — max 100/page, use pageInfo cursor).
   b) Top-level/high-level review comments — fetch all reviews via `gh api repos/BillChirico/bills-bot/pulls/{number}/reviews` and look for CHANGES_REQUESTED or COMMENT reviews whose body contains actionable feedback NOT already addressed by subsequent commits. Compare the review's commit_id against HEAD to see if new commits exist after the review.
4) If no unresolved threads AND no unaddressed high-level review comments on eligible PRs: respond exactly `NO_REPLY`.
5) If unresolved threads or unaddressed high-level comments exist:
   - Spawn ONE sub-agent PER PR (parallel), never batch PRs together.
   - Use agentId `build`, model `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6`, thinking `high`.
   - Include full unresolved thread details (thread id, file path, line, issue summary).
   - Include any unaddressed high-level review comment bodies and their review IDs.
   - Instruct spawned agents to read and follow CODING.md, fix all review comments (including nitpicks unless nonsensical/breaking/redundant), run tests/coverage, resolve threads.
   - Instruct spawned agents NOT to post PR summary comments unless Bill explicitly asks.
   - Have spawned agents report completion summary back to parent agent.
   - After spawning, send Bill a concise Discord DM status update:
     - channel: discord
     - target: user:191633014441115648
     - accountId: pip-build
     - include PR numbers, unresolved thread counts, and high-level comment counts.
6) If any spawned run fails/stalls, note it in DM and respawn once.

Keep updates concise and action-oriented.
Current time: Tuesday, February 17th, 2026 — 9:19 PM (America/New_York)

python3 - <<'PY'
import json, subprocess, os, re, textwrap

REPO='BillChirico/bills-bot'
OWNER='BillChirico'
NAME='bills-bot'

# Explicit allowlist for eligible PR authors
ELIGIBLE_AUTHORS={
    'BillChirico',
    'pip-build',
    'pip-build[bot]',
    'pipbuild',
    'PipBuild',
    'openclaw-build',
    'openclaw-build[bot]',
    'pip-build-agent',
    'pip-build-agent[bot]'
}


def run(cmd):
    p=subprocess.run(cmd, shell=True, text=True, capture_output=True)
    if p.returncode!=0:
        raise RuntimeError(f"cmd failed: {cmd}\nstdout={p.stdout}\nstderr={p.stderr}")
    return p.stdout

prs=json.loads(run(f"gh pr list --repo {REPO} --state open --json number,title,author,headRefOid,url"))

eligible=[]
skipped=[]
for pr in prs:
    login=(pr.get('author') or {}).get('login')
    if login in ELIGIBLE_AUTHORS:
        eligible.append(pr)
    else:
        skipped.append({'number':pr['number'],'author':login,'title':pr['title']})


def gql_review_threads(pr_number):
    after='null'
    unresolved=[]
    head_oid=None
    while True:
        query='''query($owner:String!,$repo:String!,$number:Int!,$after:String){\n  repository(owner:$owner,name:$repo){\n    pullRequest(number:$number){\n      commits(last:1){nodes{commit{oid}}}\n      reviewThreads(first:100, after:$after){\n        nodes{\n          id\n          isResolved\n          path\n          line\n          originalLine\n          comments(first:50){\n            nodes{\n              body\n              author{login}\n              url\n              createdAt\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        pageInfo{hasNextPage endCursor}\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}'''
        vars_obj={'owner':OWNER,'repo':NAME,'number':pr_number,'after':None if after=='null' else after}
        # pass vars via --raw-field for simplicity
        v=json.dumps(vars_obj)
        out=run(f"gh api graphql -f query='{query}' -f variables='{v}'")
        data=json.loads(out)
        pr=data['data']['repository']['pullRequest']
        if head_oid is None:
            commits=pr.get('commits',{}).get('nodes',[])
            if commits:
                head_oid=commits[0]['commit']['oid']
        threads=pr['reviewThreads']['nodes']
        for t in threads:
            if not t.get('isResolved',False):
                comments=t.get('comments',{}).get('nodes',[])
                summary=''
                if comments:
                    body=(comments[-1].get('body') or '').strip()
                    body_one=' '.join(body.split())
                    summary=body_one[:300]
                unresolved.append({
                    'thread_id': t.get('id'),
                    'path': t.get('path'),
                    'line': t.get('line') if t.get('line') is not None else t.get('originalLine'),
                    'summary': summary,
                    'comment_url': comments[-1].get('url') if comments else None,
                    'comment_author': comments[-1].get('author',{}).get('login') if comments else None,
                })
        pi=pr['reviewThreads']['pageInfo']
        if pi['hasNextPage']:
            after=pi['endCursor']
        else:
            break
    return unresolved, head_oid


def is_actionable(body:str)->bool:
    if not body:
        return False
    b=body.strip()
    if not b:
        return False
    low=b.lower()
    non_actionable_markers=[
        'lgtm',
        'looks good',
        'ship it',
        'great work',
        'approved'
    ]
    if any(m in low for m in non_actionable_markers) and len(low) < 120:
        return False
    # default: treat as actionable if substantial text
    return True


def fetch_reviews(pr_number):
    out=run(f"gh api --paginate repos/{REPO}/pulls/{pr_number}/reviews?per_page=100")
    # gh --paginate concatenates JSON arrays one after another? Usually prints each page json array newline.
    text=out.strip()
    if not text:
        return []
    reviews=[]
    # handle potentially multiple JSON arrays separated by newlines
    for part in re.split(r'\n(?=\[)', text):
        part=part.strip()
        if not part:
            continue
        arr=json.loads(part)
        if isinstance(arr,list):
            reviews.extend(arr)
    return reviews

results=[]
for pr in eligible:
    number=pr['number']
    unresolved, head_oid = gql_review_threads(number)
    reviews = fetch_reviews(number)
    unaddressed=[]
    for r in reviews:
        state=r.get('state')
        if state not in ('CHANGES_REQUESTED','COMMENT'):
            continue
        body=(r.get('body') or '').strip()
        if not is_actionable(body):
            continue
        review_commit=r.get('commit_id')
        has_new_commits = bool(review_commit and head_oid and review_commit != head_oid)
        if has_new_commits:
            continue
        unaddressed.append({
            'review_id': r.get('id'),
            'state': state,
            'author': (r.get('user') or {}).get('login'),
            'submitted_at': r.get('submitted_at'),
            'commit_id': review_commit,
            'body': body[:2000],
        })
    results.append({
        'number': number,
        'title': pr['title'],
        'url': pr['url'],
        'author': (pr.get('author') or {}).get('login'),
        'head_oid': head_oid,
        'unresolved_threads': unresolved,
        'unaddressed_high_level_reviews': unaddressed,
    })

payload={
    'open_pr_count': len(prs),
    'eligible_count': len(eligible),
    'eligible_authors': sorted(list(ELIGIBLE_AUTHORS)),
    'skipped_prs': skipped,
    'results': results,
}
print(json.dumps(payload, indent=2))
PY
